<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="153" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Yaginuma" baseAuthorityYear="1952" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Meotipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meotipa argyrodiformis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Meotipa argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2A-H</figureCitation>
) in: having the abdomen pointed to a tubercle posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1B</figureCitation>
), lacking obvious copulatory openings, and having a spoon-shaped conductor in the male palp. However, it can be distinguished from the latter by the following combination of characters: (1) the abdomen extends beyond spinnerets ~ 3/4 of total abdomen length in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1A</figureCitation>
), but less than half in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2A</figureCitation>
); (2) the epigynum does not have a tongue-shaped apophysis posteriorly and medially in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1D</figureCitation>
), but has in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2D</figureCitation>
); (3) the copulatory ducts are tube-shaped in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1F</figureCitation>
), but spherical in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2F</figureCitation>
); (4) the cymbium is long and nearly ovoid in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshida, H" journalOrPublisher="Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" refId="B21" refString="Yoshida, H, 2003. The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan. Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" title="The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan." year="2003">Yoshida 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 345), but shorter and nearly spherical in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshida, H" journalOrPublisher="Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" refId="B21" refString="Yoshida, H, 2003. The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan. Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" title="The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan." year="2003">Yoshida 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 342); (5) the embolus is long with a twisted tip, extending beyond conductor in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshida, H" journalOrPublisher="Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" refId="B21" refString="Yoshida, H, 2003. The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan. Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" title="The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan." year="2003">Yoshida 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 345), but short and straight, completely surrounded by conductor in 
<taxonomicName genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Yoshida, H" journalOrPublisher="Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" refId="B21" refString="Yoshida, H, 2003. The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan. Arachnological Society of Japan, Hokkaido" title="The spider family Theridiidae (Arachnida: Araneae) from Japan." year="2003">Yoshida 2003</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 342).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Yaginuma" baseAuthorityYear="1952" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Meotipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meotipa argyrodiformis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Meotipa argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Yaginuma, 1952) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">A-C</emphasis>
